Method Detail

generateNewKeysAndMP3Parameters

public static java.lang.Object[][] generateNewKeysAndMP3Parameters(int[][] keySizes)
                                                            throws java.security.GeneralSecurityException
This method generates new ElGamal keys and MP3 parameters for the requested key sizes.

Parameters:
keySizes - the key size generation parameters
Returns:
an Object[] containing in each entry another Object[] with tree elements. The first element is the an ElGamalKeyPair; the second is a MP3Parameters with the BASE_VOTE_GENERATOR set to the key parameter g; and the third element are another MP3Parameters with a BASE_VOTE_GENERATOR different from the key parameter g.
Throws:
java.security.GeneralSecurityException - if an error occurs in the generation process

getStaticKeysAndMP3Parameters

public static java.lang.Object[][] getStaticKeysAndMP3Parameters()
This method returns default static keys and MP3 parameters for the test keys sizes defined in the testKeySizes array.

Returns:
an Object[] containing in each entry another Object[] with tree elements. The first element is the an ElGamalKeyPair; the second is a MP3Parameters with the BASE_VOTE_GENERATOR set to the key parameter g; and the third element are another MP3Parameters with a BASE_VOTE_GENERATOR different from the key parameter g.
